### Optimizations Applied

**1. Customer Filter Parallelization (Lines 166-199)**
- **Problem:** Original code used `#pragma omp critical` causing severe lock contention on 64 cores
- **Solution:** Implemented thread-local aggregation pattern
  - Each thread collects matching customer keys in its own local vector (no synchronization)
  - Single-threaded merge phase merges all local vectors into final hash table
- **Expected impact:** Near-linear speedup from parallelism (10-30x faster on 64 cores)

**2. Orders Filter & Join Parallelization (Lines 225-258)**
- **Problem:** Original code was single-threaded linear scan with hash table insertions
- **Solution:** Implemented thread-local hash table aggregation
  - Each thread builds its own local `unordered_map` without contention
  - Single-threaded merge phase combines all local maps
  - Pre-sized hash tables to reduce rehashing overhead
- **Expected impact:** Near-linear speedup from parallelism (10-30x faster on 64 cores)

